cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.FL, cs.SE

The paper presents a new extension to the lambda calculus that allows for programming and reasoning with guarded recursion for coinductive types. This topic is relevant to several areas of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), type theory (cs.TL), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), and software engineering (cs.SE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
